To investigate whether liraglutide could reduce Ab deposition in
T2DM mice, the expression of Ab was measured by Western blots.
As shown in Fig. 4E, the Ab expression was signiﬁcantly increased in
T2DM mice. However, liraglutide could reduce the expression of Ab
protein. These results suggested that liraglutide could reduce the
Ab deposition.
3.7. Liraglutide inhibits high glucose (HG)-induced damage of
primary cortical neurons
The CCK-8 kit was used to examine whether liraglutide affected
the extent of HG-induced (50 mmol/L for 48 h) primary cortical
neurons damage. Primary cortical neurons were co-treated with
different concentrations of liraglutide (1, 10, 100, 500, 1000 nmol/L)
and/or glucose (50 mmol/L) for 48 h. As shown in Fig. 5, liraglutide
protected the primary cortical neurons stimulated with HG in a
concentration-dependent manner. When treated with 100 nmol/L
liraglutide, the cell viability of HG-induced primary cortical
